2. **Collect Lower Available Bits**: Collect all bit positions less than the highest bit where x has a 0. These bits can be used to form smaller increments in the array.
3. **Form Elements Using Available Bits**: For each position in a binary representation of numbers from 0 to n-1, map each bit to the available bits (both lower and higher than the highest bit of x) to form the elements of the array. This ensures each element is strictly increasing and maintains the required bitwise AND result.

